        <tr class='athing comtr ' id='16525769'><td>
            <table border='0'>  <tr>    <td class='ind'><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="40"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks"><center><a id='up_16525769' href='vote?id=16525769&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D16523037'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead">
          <a href="user?id=gkya" class="hnuser">gkya</a> <span class="age"><a href="item?id=16525769">11 hours ago</a></span> <span id="unv_16525769"></span><span class="par"></span> <a class="togg" n="2" href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return toggle(event, 16525769)"></a>          <span class='storyon'></span>
                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">&gt; I finally realized, after years of using make and then learning pattern rules, that the three autovars listed here are visual mnemonics. $@ looks like a target, a ring with a bullseye. $&lt; is pointing left, so it&#x27;s the first prereq. $^ is like a horizontal bracket that groups all prereqs.<p>I&#x27;ve been illuminated, sincerely!  Meanwhile, bmake has some more memorable synonyms for them like &quot;.TARGET&quot; and &quot;.ALLSRC&quot;.<span>
              </span><div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
