                  <span class="c00"><i>&gt; The killer feature of snakemake for me is that it can run a workflow on a single core or as many as you give it, or in the case of a cluster it can actually submit jobs to a queue and wait for them to finish before submitting more.</i><p>Other than your cluster example isn&#x27;t this the same as passing -j to make to run jobs in parallel?<span>
              </span><div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
