                  <span class="c00">Make doesn&#x27;t handle filenames with spaces (ASCII 32) at all!  I wrote the article (<a href="http:&#x2F;&#x2F;boston.conman.org&#x2F;2018&#x2F;02&#x2F;28.2" rel="nofollow">http:&#x2F;&#x2F;boston.conman.org&#x2F;2018&#x2F;02&#x2F;28.2</a>) about using the non-breaking space (NBSP, Unicode 160) in filenames, and make (as well as nearly everything else I tried) accepted it just fine.<p>But popular consensus (from here and Lobsters) seemed to be &quot;avoid any type of space at all cost and do not speak of it again!&quot;.  Pity.<span>
